            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "It's not really `get_flashed_messages` doing it. It's just that flash messages don't persist beyond the next request, regardless if you display them all not.\n\nI assumed this is known. Although docs for `get_flashed_messages` hint at the fact only indirectly (\"This [`category_filter`] allows rendering categories in separate html blocks\"), the [short tutorial they reference](http://flask.pocoo.org/docs/patterns/flashing/#message-flashing-pattern) makes it pretty clear the messages are not persistent in any shape or form.\n"
